    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 is a superlative example of the FD3S platform, preserved in collector-grade condition. The 13B-REW rotary powerplant maintains exceptional compression across all faces, feeding a factory-spec sequential twin-turbocharger system that provides a linear torque curve and crisp transient response. Power is delivered through a precise five-speed short-throw manual gearbox to a Torsen limited-slip rear differential. The chassis remains structurally pristine, featuring its original four-wheel double-wishbone suspension and a perfect 50/50 weight distribution for unrivaled lateral grip and turn-in precision. Every vacuum line has been inspected for integrity, and the cooling system is optimized for peak thermal efficiency. With zero evidence of oxidation or mechanical fatigue, this is a turnkey specimen for the discerning purist seeking a peak-era analog driving experience.",
      "price": 44500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
